104
00:07:07,614 --> 00:07:09,413
I want it to be a bit more lively.

105
00:07:09,414 --> 00:07:10,414
Right, right.

106
00:07:10,415 --> 00:07:12,313
Could it be him?

107
00:07:12,314 --> 00:07:15,313
Yes, he's the one with the perfect-pitch.

108
00:07:15,314 --> 00:07:19,213
He is a genius composer and in charge of soundtracks for several dramas.

109
00:07:19,214 --> 00:07:22,114
He's Kyosuke Haga, my uncle.

110
00:07:29,314 --> 00:07:30,413
Are you talking about me?

111
00:07:30,414 --> 00:07:33,413
Yes?

112
00:07:33,414 --> 00:07:36,913
Can you tell me what the notes are?

113
00:07:36,914 --> 00:07:38,913
Uncle.

114
00:07:38,914 --> 00:07:41,313
How did you like what I played?

115
00:07:41,314 --> 00:07:45,613
It was good, although you were 1/4th pitch flat on a note.

116
00:07:45,614 --> 00:07:48,013
I prefer it that way, though.

117
00:07:48,014 --> 00:07:49,814
Thank you!

118
00:07:52,014 --> 00:07:54,013
Yes, hello.

119
00:07:54,014 --> 00:07:56,413
You mean that piece.

120
00:07:56,414 --> 00:07:59,313
I'd like to break the notes up a bit more.

121
00:07:59,314 --> 00:08:01,513
Can you handle it?

122
00:08:01,514 --> 00:08:03,313
What I'm trying to say is...

123
00:08:03,314 --> 00:08:05,613
Furuto!

124
00:08:05,614 --> 00:08:08,013
Where are you?

125
00:08:08,014 --> 00:08:09,214
Furuto!

126
00:08:10,214 --> 00:08:11,913
Grandmother?

127
00:08:11,914 --> 00:08:14,413
I hear the sound of the violin playing.

128
00:08:14,414 --> 00:08:16,013
"Ayane Shitara (68)" -Furuto, don't hide.

129
00:08:16,014 --> 00:08:17,613
"Choichiro's wife" -and come out here.

130
00:08:17,614 --> 00:08:19,613
Grandmother, not again.

131
00:08:19,614 --> 00:08:22,313
Father passed away last year today,

132
00:08:22,314 --> 00:08:23,813
have you forgotten?

133
00:08:23,814 --> 00:08:25,313
Last year today?

134
00:08:25,314 --> 00:08:28,213
No, Furuto is still...

135
00:08:28,214 --> 00:08:30,713
Hey, Ayane, how unsightly!

136
00:08:30,714 --> 00:08:31,913
Grandfather.

137
00:08:31,914 --> 00:08:35,213
"Choichiro Shitara (72)" -Going after the shadow of the dead for so long.

138
00:08:35,214 --> 00:08:38,013
"The head of the Shitara family" -Our son Furuto has returned to dust.

139
00:08:38,014 --> 00:08:40,213
Don't you understand after all this time!

140
00:08:40,214 --> 00:08:44,113
Grandfather, you were told by the doctor not to walk around.

141
00:08:44,114 --> 00:08:45,813
-Mr. Mouri. -Yes.

142
00:08:45,814 --> 00:08:49,713
I'm sorry but I'm going to take care of the two for now,

143
00:08:49,714 --> 00:08:51,313
so I'll meet you at the main house later.

144
00:08:51,314 --> 00:08:53,313
I'd like to talk to you there.

145
00:08:53,314 --> 00:08:55,314
I've got something I'd like to show you.

146
00:09:24,914 --> 00:09:28,213
This violin seems to have been used over a long period of time.

147
00:09:28,214 --> 00:09:32,413
Yes, it's been made about 300 year ago.

148
00:09:32,414 --> 00:09:35,214
This sure is some antique then.

149
00:09:40,314 --> 00:09:42,613
The one who made it is an Italian

150
00:09:42,614 --> 00:09:44,814
by the name of Antonio Stradivari.

151
00:09:45,814 --> 00:09:48,513
Stradivari...

152
00:09:48,514 --> 00:09:49,813
You mean that famous...

153
00:09:49,814 --> 00:09:51,413
Just as I thought.

154
00:09:51,414 --> 00:09:53,813
Stradivarius?

155
00:09:53,814 --> 00:09:57,613
Doesn't this cost several billion yen?

156
00:09:57,614 --> 00:10:01,213
The legendary and famed musical instrument.

157
00:10:01,214 --> 00:10:03,613
Let go of it, Dad, quickly!

158
00:10:03,614 --> 00:10:06,013
My body's frozen in place that I,

159
00:10:06,014 --> 00:10:07,713
I can't let go of it.

160
00:10:07,714 --> 00:10:10,714
-What? Oh come on. -Yes. Yes.

161
00:10:17,014 --> 00:10:18,113
And...

162
00:10:18,114 --> 00:10:21,313
what about this legendary musical instrument?

163
00:10:21,314 --> 00:10:22,314
Well...

164
00:10:23,814 --> 00:10:26,913
This violin is what Danjiro Shitara,

165
00:10:26,914 --> 00:10:29,713
Uncle Kyosuke Haga's father had given as a gift

166
00:10:29,714 --> 00:10:34,313
to Grandfather Choichiro, his older brother.

167
00:10:34,314 --> 00:10:36,613
Despite being the son of blood-related brothers,

168
00:10:36,614 --> 00:10:38,913
why is his last name Haga?

169
00:10:38,914 --> 00:10:41,813
Yes, the thing is unfortunately, on the day of his birthday,

170
00:10:41,814 --> 00:10:43,913
Danjiro was attacked by a robber.

171
00:10:43,914 --> 00:10:45,413
Robber?

172
00:10:45,414 --> 00:10:47,513
Grandfather Choichiro and the others

173
00:10:47,514 --> 00:10:50,013
gave in quietly and was tied up so they were fine,

174
00:10:50,014 --> 00:10:52,513
but Danjiro resisted

175
00:10:52,514 --> 00:10:54,713
so he passed away a few days later

176
00:10:54,714 --> 00:10:57,913
because of the blow he incurred during the robbery.

177
00:10:57,914 --> 00:10:59,813
Uncle Kyosuke who was left behind,

178
00:10:59,814 --> 00:11:01,913
was adopted by the family on his mother's side

179
00:11:01,914 --> 00:11:04,613
and took after the surname Haga.

180
00:11:04,614 --> 00:11:06,213
I see.

181
00:11:06,214 --> 00:11:09,513
But, it's a amazing that this wasn't stolen.

182
00:11:09,514 --> 00:11:13,813
I mean the robber was probably after the Stradivarius.

183
00:11:13,814 --> 00:11:16,113
The robber seems to have taken the wrong violin.

184
00:11:16,114 --> 00:11:18,713
Since the Shitara Family has been musicians for generations.

185
00:11:18,714 --> 00:11:21,513
There were many violins.

186
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:24,414
It all happened 30 years ago though.

187
00:11:25,614 --> 00:11:27,613
Don't tell me that you want me to find out

188
00:11:27,614 --> 00:11:30,413
who the robber that broke in here 30 years ago was?

189
00:11:30,414 --> 00:11:32,613
No, what I'd like to ask you to do is...

190
00:11:32,614 --> 00:11:34,613
to solve the shuddering incidents,

191
00:11:34,614 --> 00:11:37,014
that have happened within the last two years.

192
00:11:41,714 --> 00:11:43,313
The first one is the incident that happened the year before last.

193
00:11:43,314 --> 00:11:46,813
Uncle Genzaburo's wife who had been very athletic,

194
00:11:46,814 --> 00:11:50,113
tripped on the stairs and passed away.

195
00:11:50,114 --> 00:11:52,813
The other one is an incident that happened last year...

196
00:11:52,814 --> 00:11:56,913
My father, Furuto leaned against a corroded fence of the veranda.

197
00:11:56,914 --> 00:11:58,813
It's unlikely that my father who was a very careful person

198
00:11:58,814 --> 00:12:00,513
would fall to his death like that.

199
00:12:00,514 --> 00:12:03,013
I just can't make myself think that something like that could happen.

200
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:05,614
I would like you to solve these hideous cases, Detective Mouri.

201
00:12:07,814 --> 00:12:10,613
Maybe those two incidents were accidents...

202
00:12:10,614 --> 00:12:15,113
No! Both of them passed away on Grandfather's birthday!

203
00:12:15,114 --> 00:12:16,513
Moreover, at this time,

204
00:12:16,514 --> 00:12:19,113
the two played this Stradivarius.

205
00:12:19,114 --> 00:12:20,913
It is as if they were cursed by the incident

206
00:12:20,914 --> 00:12:22,913
that occurred 30 years ago.

207
00:12:22,914 --> 00:12:25,613
And, this year, I'm going to be playing it...

208
00:12:25,614 --> 00:12:28,313
I'm sure that something bad will happen to me too.

209
00:12:28,314 --> 00:12:30,314
Then, don't play it.

210
00:12:31,314 --> 00:12:32,714
I want to play it!

211
00:12:33,914 --> 00:12:37,213
But, if you can take it out freely like this anytime,

212
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:39,313
you can play it any time you like, can't you?

213
00:12:39,314 --> 00:12:41,313
I can't take it out freely.

214
00:12:41,314 --> 00:12:45,113
I borrowed it from Grandfather just for today

215
00:12:45,114 --> 00:12:47,713
for this special occasion so I can practice.

216
00:12:47,714 --> 00:12:48,814
That's why...

217
00:12:53,414 --> 00:12:56,413
See, I'm sure he's watching me.

218
00:12:56,414 --> 00:12:58,213
Then, you mean the violin that I played

219
00:12:58,214 --> 00:13:00,113
a little a while ago wasn't supposed to be...

220
00:13:00,114 --> 00:13:01,814
Of course it's a secret.

221
00:13:02,914 --> 00:13:05,713
And, what would you like me to do?

222
00:13:05,714 --> 00:13:08,013
I want you to undo the curse of this Stradivarius

223
00:13:08,014 --> 00:13:09,714
before I begin playing it.

224
00:13:11,214 --> 00:13:12,813
A curse is not something

225
00:13:12,814 --> 00:13:16,013
