245
00:14:37,928 --> 00:14:39,827
What? Grandmother is upstairs.

246
00:14:39,828 --> 00:14:41,527
Where is the room upstairs?

247
00:14:41,528 --> 00:14:43,628
The room at the very end of the 3rd floor.

248
00:14:48,628 --> 00:14:50,127
This is impossible, unless we have a fire-proof suit or something.

249
00:14:50,128 --> 00:14:51,128
Oh no.

250
00:15:04,028 --> 00:15:06,227
I can't help myself for being the way I am.

251
00:15:06,228 --> 00:15:07,728
Take care of everyone else, will you?

252
00:15:08,828 --> 00:15:09,828
Uncle.

253
00:15:09,829 --> 00:15:14,227
Pops, please park your car below that window, quick!

254
00:15:14,228 --> 00:15:15,228
Do that, okay?

255
00:15:15,229 --> 00:15:17,528
Hey, you! Wait, it's dangerous.

256
00:15:27,228 --> 00:15:28,627
Are you all right?

257
00:15:28,628 --> 00:15:30,628
Grandfather, please get a hold of yourself.

258
00:15:37,128 --> 00:15:39,627
Hey, Dad, wait, just what do you think you're doing?

259
00:15:39,628 --> 00:15:40,828
Beats me!

260
00:15:45,128 --> 00:15:48,527
That kid told me to park my car here.

261
00:15:48,528 --> 00:15:51,028
How come I'm listening to that kid?

262
00:16:23,628 --> 00:16:24,628
What?

263
00:16:30,028 --> 00:16:32,027
Hey, get a hold of yourself, Aunty!

264
00:16:32,028 --> 00:16:33,028
Mrs. Shitara!

265
00:16:36,828 --> 00:16:40,227
I see, he wanted to reduce the distance of the fall with the car

266
00:16:40,228 --> 00:16:41,827
and used the roof as cushion.

267
00:16:41,828 --> 00:16:44,027
Just what a kid would think of.

268
00:16:44,028 --> 00:16:45,427
We were lucky that we got a wagon

269
00:16:45,428 --> 00:16:47,927
because they had nothing else.

270
00:16:47,928 --> 00:16:49,827
It's a rental car, you know!

271
00:16:49,828 --> 00:16:52,728
Who knows how much we're going to have to pay for repair.

272
00:16:53,928 --> 00:16:56,727
The fire engines soon arrived at the scene but...

273
00:16:56,728 --> 00:17:00,627
the annex of the Shitara family kept on burning for a while.

274
00:17:00,628 --> 00:17:06,128
As if it were grieving the postlude of the conductor Genzaburo Shitara.

275
00:17:13,428 --> 00:17:15,427
No!

276
00:17:15,428 --> 00:17:18,727
But, we've got to treat you at the hospital either way.

277
00:17:18,728 --> 00:17:20,427
No, no!

278
00:17:20,428 --> 00:17:24,327
I'm sorry, but could you let her have her way, please.

279
00:17:24,328 --> 00:17:28,127
A year ago, our son was taken away on the ambulance

280
00:17:28,128 --> 00:17:30,927
and never came back.

281
00:17:30,928 --> 00:17:33,827
I guess she doesn't want to ride the same vehicle.

282
00:17:33,828 --> 00:17:38,528
Could you please treat her at home just for today?

283
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:44,627
Thank you, sonny.

284
00:17:44,628 --> 00:17:46,527
I'm sorry for what you had to go through too, Kyosuke.

285
00:17:46,528 --> 00:17:47,927
Thank you.

286
00:17:47,928 --> 00:17:49,028
No problem.

287
00:17:50,828 --> 00:17:53,227
Little Kyosuke, are you all right?

288
00:17:53,228 --> 00:17:54,527
I'm fine.

289
00:17:54,528 --> 00:17:57,627
Will you please cut out that "Little" when calling me?

290
00:17:57,628 --> 00:18:00,028
30 years have gone by all ready.

291
00:18:03,328 --> 00:18:05,127
The steward, Ms. Tsumagari

292
00:18:05,128 --> 00:18:09,027
was originally working at Uncle Kyosuke's house.

293
00:18:09,028 --> 00:18:12,227
But, 30 years ago after that robbery,

294
00:18:12,228 --> 00:18:14,227
when Danjiro and his wife passed away,

295
00:18:14,228 --> 00:18:15,927
and Uncle Kyosuke who was left behind

296
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:17,927
took after the Haga family name,

297
00:18:17,928 --> 00:18:19,827
we had Ms. Tsumagari come to work for us,

298
00:18:19,828 --> 00:18:21,627
and she's been with us since.

299
00:18:21,628 --> 00:18:25,227
Kyosuke's father was not the only one who passed away?

300
00:18:25,228 --> 00:18:26,327
No.

301
00:18:26,328 --> 00:18:30,727
His mother Chiha, was not a very healthy person to begin with,

302
00:18:30,728 --> 00:18:33,727
but she watched over her husband Danjiro without sleeping...

303
00:18:33,728 --> 00:18:37,427
As a result, she fell ill of extreme fatigue and...

304
00:18:37,428 --> 00:18:40,527
And, what about your mother, Hasuki?

305
00:18:40,528 --> 00:18:42,827
She got a divorce and went back to her parental home,

306
00:18:42,828 --> 00:18:46,227
just before Grandfather's birthday 2 years ago.

307
00:18:46,228 --> 00:18:51,127
That's why Great Aunty Eimi ended up playing for his birthday,

308
00:18:51,128 --> 00:18:53,427
since it was Grandfather's 70th birthday

309
00:18:53,428 --> 00:18:55,727
as well as to encourage Father.

310
00:18:55,728 --> 00:18:59,727
She was to play that Stradivarius that had been sealed for 30 years.

311
00:18:59,728 --> 00:19:01,627
That famed musical instrument was sealed?

312
00:19:01,628 --> 00:19:04,827
Yes. When Grandfather received it from Danjiro,

313
00:19:04,828 --> 00:19:07,428
he was very happy but...

314
00:19:08,928 --> 00:19:12,327
My father who borrowed it when he was 18 years old,

315
00:19:12,328 --> 00:19:13,627
and performed in a contest

316
00:19:13,628 --> 00:19:15,627
experienced the strings snapping apart twice on stage,

317
00:19:15,628 --> 00:19:17,527
and was disqualified.

318
00:19:17,528 --> 00:19:18,727
Yet, on another occasion,

319
00:19:18,728 --> 00:19:22,427
my aunt who was scheduled to perform on a certain TV program,

320
00:19:22,428 --> 00:19:26,327
came down with a high fever right before show time.

321
00:19:26,328 --> 00:19:29,327
And, Great Uncle Genzaburo, who was on his way to a concert abroad,

322
00:19:29,328 --> 00:19:32,227
came down with a serious case of tenosynovitis during practice.

323
00:19:32,228 --> 00:19:36,027
I see. I can see why you'd want to seal it.

324
00:19:36,028 --> 00:19:39,427
You think the violin's okay?

325
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:42,028
It was left on the desk in the room as is.

326
00:19:43,828 --> 00:19:45,827
If this fire was a case of arson,

327
00:19:45,828 --> 00:19:47,727
it could've been taken during all this commotion.

328
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:49,327
No, it wasn't.

329
00:19:49,328 --> 00:19:52,627
I put it back in the storage room right away.

330
00:19:52,628 --> 00:19:55,327
Or, do I look like an incompetent steward

331
00:19:55,328 --> 00:19:59,027
who would leave such a famed musical instrument unattended in a household

332
00:19:59,028 --> 00:20:00,928
where outsiders are walking around?

333
00:20:01,928 --> 00:20:02,928
Oh, well... No.

334
00:20:02,929 --> 00:20:05,227
Besides, the fire was not caused by arson,

335
00:20:05,228 --> 00:20:06,428
but rather, smoking while sleeping.

336
00:20:07,428 --> 00:20:08,627
It seems that the area around the ashtray

337
00:20:08,628 --> 00:20:11,027
that was in that room is where the fire started,

338
00:20:11,028 --> 00:20:13,527
and the door was torn off with the key locked.

339
00:20:13,528 --> 00:20:15,827
You're the one who broke it down, right?

340
00:20:15,828 --> 00:20:18,027
If so, the room was locked

341
00:20:18,028 --> 00:20:19,627
and arson would be impossible.

342
00:20:19,628 --> 00:20:21,327
Oh, is that right.

343
00:20:21,328 --> 00:20:25,027
Well, please be extremely careful when smoking.

344
00:20:25,028 --> 00:20:27,927
It's best not to smoke though.

345
00:20:27,928 --> 00:20:30,028
Yeah, that's right.

346
00:20:31,328 --> 00:20:34,127
But, even if everything were to be a coincidence,

347
00:20:34,128 --> 00:20:35,627
it sure is frightening.

348
00:20:35,628 --> 00:20:36,827
To think that something would happen

349
00:20:36,828 --> 00:20:38,227
on the same day for three consecutive years.

350
00:20:38,228 --> 00:20:39,627
Yes.

351
00:20:39,628 --> 00:20:45,827
Including Kyosuke's father who died in the robbery 30 years ago,

352
00:20:45,828 --> 00:20:47,927
it comes up to a total of four all together.

353
00:20:47,928 --> 00:20:49,127
Taking this into consideration,

354
00:20:49,128 --> 00:20:54,727
I think you should stop celebrating Choichiro's birthday from next year.

355
00:20:54,728 --> 00:20:57,427
I tell you, he's already smoking.

356
00:20:57,428 --> 00:21:00,127
Well, it'll turn out that way anyway,

357
00:21:00,128 --> 00:21:01,927
because Uncle has bad lungs

358
00:21:01,928 --> 00:21:05,027
and has only a half a year to live.

359
00:21:05,028 --> 00:21:06,527
Really?

360
00:21:06,528 --> 00:21:10,827
Yes. I wanted to at least celebrate today with him.

361
00:21:10,828 --> 00:21:12,627
We can't anymore,

362
00:21:12,628 --> 00:21:15,427
because he's already gone to bed.

363
00:21:15,428 --> 00:21:18,827
The Mrs. has already been treated and has also gone to bed.

364
00:21:18,828 --> 00:21:22,527
So, since this doesn't seem to be a case or anything,

365
00:21:22,528 --> 00:21:24,528
we'll start off home too.

366
00:21:31,128 --> 00:21:33,727
Who's cigarette butt is this?

367
00:21:33,728 --> 00:21:36,627
It doesn't seem to be yours, Pops.

368
00:21:36,628 --> 00:21:38,727
That brand is the one...

369
00:21:38,728 --> 00:21:41,127
that Great Uncle Genzaburo used to smoke.

370
00:21:41,128 --> 00:21:42,527
Come to think of it,

371
00:21:42,528 --> 00:21:45,927
he stopped by here before going to the annex.

372
00:21:45,928 --> 00:21:47,727
If so, then...

373
00:21:47,728 --> 00:21:49,028
this is...

374
00:21:52,928 --> 00:21:54,028
Conan?

375
00:21:57,228 --> 00:21:59,628
Kid, where do you think you're going?

376
00:22:15,228 --> 00:22:16,928
Just as I thought.

377
00:22:20,228 --> 00:22:24,027
This is not an accident, but murder.

378
00:22:24,028 --> 00:22:27,127
Moreover, if my deduction is correct,

379
00:22:27,128 --> 00:22:29,128
the next target is...

380
00:23:57,628 --> 00:24:02,027
"Next Episode."

381
00:24:02,028 --> 00:24:05,527
This could be a serial murder case.

382
00:24:05,528 --> 00:24:07,727
What?

383
00:24:07,728 --> 00:24:09,127
Wait!

384
00:24:09,128 --> 00:24:11,427
D-E-F-G...

385
00:24:11,428 --> 00:24:15,227
then the next target is Hasuki with the initial H.

386
00:24:15,228 --> 00:24:18,328
Oh no! She shouldn't be left alone!

387
00:24:22,028 --> 00:24:23,627
Next Conan,

388
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:27,528
"Cacophony of Stradivarius! Interlude!"

389
00:24:43,328 --> 00:24:45,827
Next Conan's Hint:

390
00:24:45,828 --> 00:24:47,827
"Initial."

391
00:24:47,828 --> 00:24:50,227
-Conan, I'm sure the murderer is the mother. -Why do you say that?

392
00:24:50,228 --> 00:24:52,628
I'm certain it's mother and child.

